summary:
I am a eager student of sociology with an undying fascination for culture. 

My greatest passion project so far - volunteering at International Animal Rescue Yayasan Indonesia has taught me more about the importance and impact of culture, power and identity than about orangutan care that I was there for. I have been studying society ever since that experience. 

Since what I am studying is my passion instead of engaging outside of university I am a part of the Honours Programme, which allows me to take up more courses and gain more knowledge. 
In my free time sip tea along a book that will take me on a trip to a different location on earth or I go hiking in the nearest forest.
